12 WHEREAS, Bob Wills, born in 1905, began playing fiddle in his
13 youth before moving with his band, the Texas Playboys, to Oklahoma
14 in 1934 to pursue business and creative opportunities; and
15 WHEREAS, Bob Wills became known as the King of Western Swing as
16 he helped originate and popularize a unique genre of music rooted in
17 folk, jazz, and blues that would lead to the development of rock and
18 roll and modern country music; and
19 WHEREAS, Bob Wills entertained millions of people during his
20 heyday â€” performing twice weekly at what would become historic
21 Cain's Ballroom in Tulsa, playing live daily radio broadcasts,
22 touring across the country, and appearing in more than a dozen
23 movies; and
